# SSE Streaming Standards

## Why streaming is required
Analysis takes 60-120 seconds. No streaming = black-box wait.
Black-box wait = users close the tab = demo fails.
(Project 1 shipped without streaming. It is required here.)

## Backend pattern (FastAPI)

POST /analyze or /generate:
  - Validate request
  - Generate job_id (uuid4)
  - Store job state in memory dict
  - Start background task (asyncio)
  - Return {job_id} immediately (< 200ms)

GET /stream/{job_id}:
  - Returns StreamingResponse with media_type="text/event-stream"
  - Emits events as agents complete:

```python
async def event_generator(job_id: str):
    # agent_complete events
    yield f"event: agent_complete\ndata: {json.dumps({agent: job_intelligence, progress: 25})}\n\n"
    yield f"event: agent_complete\ndata: {json.dumps({agent: rate_intelligence, progress: 50})}\n\n"
    yield f"event: agent_complete\ndata: {json.dumps({agent: proposal_analyst, progress: 75})}\n\n"
    yield f"event: agent_complete\ndata: {json.dumps({agent: win_strategy, progress: 100})}\n\n"
    # final complete event
    yield f"event: complete\ndata: {report_json}\n\n"
```

## Event schema
agent_complete: {"agent": str, "progress": int (25/50/75/100)}
complete:       ProposalReport as JSON string
error:          {"message": str}

